Key Match Events: Jackson Chourio hit a leadoff triple in the bottom of the ninth inning.
Jake Bauers hit a walk-off single to win the game for the Brewers.
Post-Match Reflections: Brewers manager Pat Murphy praised Bob Uecker as an epitome of a champion.
Jackson Chourio expressed that this was the most fun celebration he has ever been a part of.
Brewers owner Mark Attanasio highlighted the organization's belief in Chourio and the risks they took.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Brewers clinched the National League Central crown with their 2-1 win over the Phillies.
Bob Uecker, 90 years old, joined the team in the clubhouse to celebrate.
The Brewers celebrated with non-alcoholic champagne and beer for the underage Chourio.
